SHEDULE MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
****************************************************
>cron job :cron job is sheduling task in linux that runs automatically specific time and interval
it managed a background service is called a cron 
>To ceate and edit the cron job
   crontab -e

>To check the list of cron tab
   crontab -l

>To remove the cron job 
   crontab -r

>To check list of cron jobs from another user 
   crontab -u username -l

  example:crontab -u jagan -l

>To create the crontab at a specific user 
   crontab -u username -e
    example:crontab -u jagan -e
    "Here we create a cron job at specific user"

>TO check the crontab is active or not 
   systemctl status crond

>Start the cronjob service
   systemctl start crond

>Enable the cron service
   systemctl enable crond

>Restart the cron service
    systemctl restart crond

>Stop cron service 
    systemctl stop crond

>How to work the cron job

* * * * * command

1) * =minutes
2) * =Hours
3) * =Day of the month
4) * =month 
5) * =Day of the week

example:
       35 11 31 3 * echo "hello jagan" >> /tmp/cron-test.txt
//Here >> is save /tmp.cron-test.txt is the place of the location

>if you create a job in root user then you switch another user the job job is cannot be remove
  command: crontab -r =to remove the job only in root user

  if you create a job another user then will remove the job 
    command :crontab -u username -r

   example: crontab -u jagan -r




           
         




































